RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHURCHILL DOWNS RACE 11 1M Turf CR: 88. Maiden Special Weight Purse 120000. FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 119 lbs. (Preference To Horses That Have Not Started For Less Than $50,000). (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One mile.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: EDGARTOWN stalked the clear leader from the two path, bid along with an outer rival entering the lane, led while battling with that one through midstretch and shook free late. SURF CITY tracked two to three wide, bid along with an inner rival entering the lane, vied through midstretch but was turned away late. DASHMAN pursued from midpack three to four wide, ranged up along with an inner pair turning for home, took aim entering the lane but only managed to chase those foes home. POLAR BEAR PLUNGE pursued two wide and between horses, chased in the three path around the far turn, ran on after being herded outwardly in midstretch and reached a dead-heat for fourth. DROBNY sped clear early on, but was headed inside of a trio of bidders entering the lane, gave way yet saved fourth via a dead heat. MONEYSHOT tracked along the inside, chased around the far turn, drifted out in midstretch and weakened. BRITISH SEA bumped with an outer rival at the start and failed to factor from the two path. TIGGEROO broke slowly, lacked speed along the inside and made little impact. EVENING NEWS bumped with an inner rival at the start, pursued along the inside and faded. UNION RUN laid off of the pace four to two wide and failed to factor. THE LOOK FACTOR showed little.
